<HEADLINE> N.Irish Police Charge Man with Police Killings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Northern Ireland police said today
they had charged a man with killing two officers who were shot in
Lurgan early last week.
</P>
<P>
"A 29 year old man has been charged with murder, two counts,"
local press quoted a security source as saying. The man was
detained on Tuesday and was due to appear later in the afternoon
at Craigavon magistrates court.
</P>
<P>
Two police were gunned down in close range in an IRA guerrilla
ambush last week while on a routine patrol. The murder has angered
the British government which cut off official contacts with Sinn
Fein, the political wing of the IRA.
</P>
<P>
The IRA has been fighting against the British rule of Northern
Ireland over the past 28 years, and more than 3,000 people have
died as a result of the conflict. 
</P>
