<HEADLINE> PLO Slams Israel for Current Middle East Tension </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Tension prevailing in the Middle
East is the result of the provocative policies of the Israeli
government of Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, said Palestinian
ambassador to Zimbabwe Ali Halimeh.
</P>
<P>
Ali Halimeh said in a statement today that the Israeli
administration was responsible for the collapse of the
negotiations between the Palestine Liberation Organization (PLO )
and the government of Israel.
</P>
<P>
"It is known to the entire world that Prime Minister Netanyahu
is not interested in a political settlement with the
Palestinians, and he himself is to blame for the deteriorating
situation in the area," said Halimeh.
</P>
<P>
"The tension which is prevailing in the Middle East is a
result of the persistent policies of Netanyahu, policies which
rejects basic principles of the Madrid peace conference and the
Oslo declaration of principles and the signed agreement between
the previous government and the PLO," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said Israel had since its formation embarked on a campaign
to destabilize the Palestinian self-ruled territories through
economic blockades, security establishment and encouraging
violence.
</P>
<P>
He said the Palestinian people were determined to continue to
fight until they achieved their objectives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
