<HEADLINE> Britain Supports Peaceful Settlement of UAE-Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Minister of State
for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs Derek Fatchett today
reiterated his country's support for UAE's efforts to settle a
territorial dispute with Iran by peaceful means.
</P>
<P>
Britain has a firm stand of backing UAE's proposal for a
peaceful settlement of the Iran-UAE dispute over three islands
known as Abu Musa and Greater and Lesser Tunbs, the UAE's Wam
news agency quoted Fatchett as saying.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks at a meeting with his UAE's counterpart
Sheikh Bin Zayed al-Nahyan. He arrived here Tuesday night for a
two-day visit to the United Arab Emirates (UAE) as part of his
Gulf tour.
</P>
<P>
Fatchett said the issue should be settled either through
negotiations between the UAE and Iran or by referring it to the
International Court of Justice in the Hague.
</P>
<P>
The islands are currently under Iran's rule, but are claimed
by the UAE. The UAE said the islands were occupied by Iran in
1981. The UAE has proposed to bring the dispute to the
International Court of Justice, but Iran has rejected the
bid. 
</P>
