<HEADLINE> Ethiopia's Regional Administration Warns Against </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The Addis Ababa regional
administration has ordered illegal constructors to evacuate
properties within 10 days from construciton sites in the region.
</P>
<P>
The administration said in a statement today that certain
individuals and companies are undertaking unlawful, extended
constructions on the plots the region planned to legally allot to
land seekers, on pretext that they have bought the construction
sites from farmers.
</P>
<P>
To address ensuing problems from illegal construction demands
quite a huge resource, and it is for this reason that the
administration is banning illegal constructions, said the
statement.
</P>
<P>
It warned that on failure to meet the deadline to move
properties, the administration will clear properties and demolish
illegal and unplanned constructions.
</P>
<P>
According to the statement, land with a capacity to settle up
to 30,000 people will be given to individuals at the end of the
year on the basis of studies conducted. The administration has
also planned to distribute land to about 50,000 people next year.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of illegal constructions have been demolished
recently in the region, according to a local report. 
</P>
