<HEADLINE> Kuwait, US to Carry out Joint Military Exercises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait and the U.S. would
carry a joint military exercise in Kuwaiti territories soon, a
press release issued by the U.S. embassy here said today.
</P>
<P>
The military maneuvers, code-named "Intrinsic Action 97-2,"
will have 1,300 U.S. troops participated and is aimed at
"improving readiness and interoperability between Kuwait and
U.S. armed forces and to enhance U.S. military force capabilities
to quickly deploy in the region," the embassy statement said.
</P>
<P>
It did not give an exact date and duration of the declared
maneuvers, but indicated that war game might be a rapid reacting
exercise.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the U.S. troops would include rapid
reaction force.
</P>
<P>
Since Kuwait and the U.S. entered a defense cooperation
agreement in 1991 after the Gulf War, dozens of various
joint military exercises have been carried out by the two
armed forces in Kuwait territories as well as in the Gulf.
</P>
<P>
Military sources at the Kuwaiti Ministry of Defense said
"Intrinsic Action 97-2" was within the frame of military
cooperation between both countries to improve the fighting
capabilities and get acquainted with the most modern military
weapons.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. presently has a military camp in northern Kuwait
where a full brigade mechanized military equipment are kept and
the U.S. troops to be involved in the maneuvers are expected to
come unarmed and use the equipment stored in the camp.
</P>
<P>
The war games are "intended to further demonstrate the
United States' commitment to the security and stability of the
Gulf Region," the U.S. embassy statement said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
