<HEADLINE> Nearly 14 Percent of Students in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 14 percent of the
students in Ethiopia is addicted to chat, a local mild
stimulant plant, the Ethiopian News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Quoting a research paper of the Ministry of Education, the
report said most of the chat addictive students are found in senior
high schools of Harer, Dire Dawa, west Addis Ababa and Agaro.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the survey was conducted in 10 senior
high schools of five administration regions. Out of the 983
students on the survey, 121 smoke cigarettes.
</P>
<P>
The survey showed 47.9 percent of the students are alcohol
drinking, of whom nearly three percent are regular drinkers.
</P>
<P>
The report urged school administrators to take measures
against the practice and help prevent drug abuse among students.
</P>
