<HEADLINE> European Shares End Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 25 (Xinhua) -- All shares on Europe's major stock
markets closed higher today.
</P>
<P>
In London, British shares went up for a second day, as
pharmaceuticals were spurred higher by rising U.S. drug stocks and
market nerves were steadied by a continued rebound on Wall Street.
The FTSE-100 closed at 4,640.0, up 43.7 points.
</P>
<P>
Shares on Frankfurt market took heart, shrugging off a weak
start on Wall Street in afternoon European trade to shoot ahead to
new records amid comfortable liquidity conditions. The DAX-30
index closed at 3,798.51, up 42.69 points. In later screen-based
trade the IBIS DAX index ended at 3,819.52, up 58.45 points.
</P>
<P>
In Paris, stocks surged three percent to an all-time closing
high, powered by gains on Wall Street, a rebound in the dollar and
higher bond prices. The CAC-40 index closed at 2,867.44, up 82.68
points.  
