<HEADLINE> Film Reception Held to Mark Hong Kong's Return to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, June 25 (Xinhua) -- A film reception was held here
this evening to mark Hong Kong's return to China.
</P>
<P>
About 300 people, including four Iraqi ministers of interior,
trade, transportation and communications, agriculture and
irrigation and six under-secretaries as well as more than 30
ambassadors, attended the reception, which was sponsored by the
Chineses Embassy.
</P>
<P>
The color documentary film "Hong Kong of China," showed with
Arabic interpretation at the five-star Mansur Hotel, depicts Hong
Kong's today and yesterday and explains how the Chinese
government has tries to keep it prosperous and stable in a long
term.
</P>
<P>
