<HEADLINE> Greek School Leavers Begin Exams for Higher Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Some 170,000 school leavers in
Greece began their national exams for higher education today.
</P>
<P>
The candidates are reportedly divided into four subject
groupings: pure sciences, life sciences, the classics and
economics-oriented exams.
</P>
<P>
They will be joined for the first time by the graduates of
technical 6th-form colleges, while "special subjects" like
languages and music will be held on July 3-9, after the mainstream
exams are over.
</P>
<P>
Every candidate is examined on four core subjects, each with
three-hour written exams.
</P>
<P>
The combined score provides the ticket to university or
polytechnic.
</P>
<P>
Greece's Education Minister Gerasimos Arsenis Tuesday urged
candidates and parents alike to be calm and collected.
</P>
<P>
The call follows fears that many candidates are overstressed.
