<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves Loans for Indonesia, Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today announced
the approval of two loans totaling 214 million U.S. dollars
equivalent to Indonesia and Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia will receive a loan of some 66.4 million dollars for
its renewable energy small power project. Additionally, the Global
Environment Facility will provide a grant of 4 million dollars for
the project.
</P>
<P>
This project will provide financing for private developers
interested in setting up renewable energy businesses, such as
retailing biomass, hydropower, and solar power systems. The
project also includes technical assistance for private developers
to ensure compliance with environmental guidelines and to help
projects move along.
</P>
<P>
The other loan of some 145 million dollars is provided to
Thailand's metropolitan distribution reinforcement project.
</P>
<P>
The project will upgrade and expand the electricity
distribution system and commercialize the Metropolitan Electricity
Authority. 
</P>
</TEXT>
