<HEADLINE> Pakistan Railways to Be Privatized: Sources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan Railways will be
privatized by June 30, 1998, under the directive of Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif, official sources said.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Railways has prepared a blue print for the
privatization of the Railways which was approved by the National
Assembly, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Under the privatization plan, the Railway's core services and
non-core services will be given to two companies separately, they
said.
</P>
<P>
The core services includes passenger, freight services and
infrastructure like railway track and railway stations while the
non-core services comprises locomotive factory, carriage workshop
and so on.
</P>
<P>
Surplus employees of the Railways, which employees 109,000,
would be offered golden handshake, retrained for other jobs or
absorbed in different departments, they said.
</P>
<P>
According to the plan, the Ministry of Railways will be
abolished and merged into the Communication Ministry, they said,
adding a separate Railway Board will be created as a separate
entity to administer the railway affairs
</P>
<P>
Also, a regulatory authority will be created to oversee and
regulate the functioning and inter-action of the railway companies
and for modernization of the whole system, they said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
