<HEADLINE> HKSAR Chief Executive on Flying National, Regional Flags (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Tung Chee Hwa, the Chief
Executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR),
today issued stipulations he will make under relevant Bills passed
by the HKSAR Provisional Legislative Council on the use of China's
national flag and emblem and the HKSAR's regional flag and emblem
in Hong Kong with effect from July 1.
</P>
<P>
According to the decision of the Chief Executive with effect
from July 1:
The national flag should fly every day at the official residence
of the Chief Executive, all border control or check points of the
HKSAR, the Hong Kong International Airport and Government House.
</P>
<P>
The national flag should fly on every working day at the
following places: the office of the Chief Executive, the Executive
Council, the Court of Final Appeal, the High Court, the
Provisional Legislative Council and Hong Kong Economic and Trade
Offices in Sydney, Brussels, Toronto, Tokyo, Singapore, London,
New York, San Francisco and Washington.
</P>
<P>
The national emblem should be displayed at the Office of the
Chief Executive.
</P>
<P>
The regional flag should fly every day at the following places:
all border control or check points of the HKSAR, the Hong Kong
International Airport, the official residence of the Chief
Executive and Government House.
The regional flag should fly every working day at the following
places: the Office of the Chief Executive, the Central Government
Offices, the Executive Council, the Provisional Legislative
Council, the Provisional Urban Council, the Provisional Regional
Council, the law courts of various levels in the HKSAR and the
Hong Kong Economic and Trade Offices in the nine foreign cities
mentioned above.
</P>
</TEXT>
