<HEADLINE> China's First Train Hospital to Leave HK on July 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 26 (Xinhua) -- China's first train equipped
with medical equipment is scheduled to leave Hong Kong on July 1,
the day when China resumes the exercise of sovereignty over Hong
Kong, to serve patients in the interior area.
</P>
<P>
The "health express", as it is called, was made in the east
port city of Qingdao with the funding of noted personalities in
Hong Kong. It will be used to treat eye disease patients in
relatively impoverished areas.
</P>
<P>
The first stop of train will Fuyang in east China's Anhui
province. During its 40-day planned stay there, ophthalmologists
on the train will perform operations on more than 800 elderly
people with cataracts for eye-sight restoration.
</P>
<P>
The train, presently parked at the Hung Hom Railway Station,
consists of rooms for performing operations, providing
consultancies, examinations, radiations and sterilization, as well
as resting rooms.
</P>
<P>
A staff of 16, including four eye experts, all from inland
areas, will work on the train.  
</P>
