<HEADLINE> Greece Says Hong Kong's Return to China Historic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Greek Foreign Minister Theodoros
Pangalos today welcomed Hong Kong's handover on July 1, saying it
was an event of historic importance.
</P>
<P>
Pangalos said in an interview with Xinhua that he believed Hong
Kong, as a significant world financial and economic center, would
continue to be prosperous and stable after the handover.
</P>
<P>
He said China had assured that the principles inscribed in
the Joint Declaration and the Basic Law would be implemented.
</P>
<P>
"We have noted China's assurances. We believe that these
principles guarantee the maintenance of stability, progress and
freedom for the people of Hong Kong," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said he believed China, whose reform and opening-up policy
has resulted in tremendous economic progress, would not change
its "one country, two systems" policy.
</P>
<P>
There were good prospects for broadening Greece's economic
cooperation with the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
