<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing University Professor Greets Hong Kong Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Huang Jiayou, dean of the
Geophysics Department at Beijing University, who was born in Hong
Kong in 1940, was excited when he learned that he does not have to
get approval from the British embassy in Beijing if he wants to
visit his elderly in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong's return is the will of all Chinese," Huang said,
recalling the first gift he received from his sister when he
visited her in Hong Kong last December, the emblem of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR).
</P>
<P>
At a symposium on Hong Kong's return, held at the university
today, Xiao Weiyun, a law professor, said that his own
understanding was that the "one country, two systems" policy was
brilliant, and marked a bright future for Hong Kong. Xiao, who is
a member of the committee drafting the Basic Law of the HKSAR,
will fly to Hong Kong tomorrow for the handover ceremony.
</P>
<P>
He said that the "one country, two systems" concept of Deng
Xiaoping has been the key to dealing with many problems he and
other lawmakers confronted with when drafting the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
Xiao expressed confidence in Hong Kong's future development and
prosperity, with Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong and the
policy of a high-degree of autonomy.
</P>
<P>
Li Yining, dean of the universiy's Guanghua Management
School, said that Hong Kong's prosperity depends on and benefits
from economic reforms in the inland areas. Li, who is an economist,
said that innovation depends on technology, a field in which Hong
Kong is not particularly strong, so it is necessary for Hong Kong
to cooperate with the inland areas for continued development.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's prosperity is good for economic reforms in the
inland. Hong Kong investors like the red chip stocks of the inland
enterprises and this relates to people's confidence in Hong Kong
after 1997, Li said.
</P>
<P>
Liang Shoude, dean of the college of international relations,
said that China is the only country with two social systems, which
is a successful solution to the Hong Kong question.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government is capable of governing Hong Kong and
governing a country with two systems, and can play an important
role in safeguarding world peace and promoting development, Liang
said.
</P>
<P>
Chi Huisheng, executive vice president of Beijing University,
said that the university will have exchanges and cooperation with
Hong Kong in education, culture, and science and technology to
contribute to Hong Kong's prosperity and stability, and that it is
ready to open training courses for civil servants in the HKSAR
government on legal and personnel systems, sociology and social
work. 
</P>
</TEXT>
