<HEADLINE> Independence And Self-Control In Chinese Christianity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Shi Zesheng, vice-chairman of
the Three-Self Patriotic Movement Committee of the Protestant
Churches of China, said today that Chinese Christianity should
develop in an independent, self-governing way.
</P>
<P>
The modern history of China is one of suffering, invasions,
oppression, enslavement, and plundering by imperialist powers, and
that some missionaries did not stick to the teachings of the
Bible, but stood on the side of the invaders instead, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Christianity, which came from the West, could not be separated
from imperialist and colonist influences, he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
"The first English missionary to China, who held a post of
vice-consul in the British Embassy in China, definitely knew about
the evil opium trade in 1840," Shi said by way of an example. He
added that several churches set up by the first US missionaries to
China were headed by British opium traders.
</P>
<P>
Foreign missionaries played an important role in the signing of
various unequal treaties, Shi pointed out.
</P>
<P>
In view of this, we should not regard Christianity in a naive
way. It is true that some foreigners preached Christianity with
pure motives at first, but their belief was distorted and
utilized for other purposes in the end, he said.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that there are still people today who are using
Christianity as a tool for anti-Chinese activities, and that "We
should not let the old image of foreign Christianity re-emerge at
the new historical era."
</P>
<P>
The principle of "self-administration, self-support, and
self-propagation" among the Protestant churches appeared shortly
after the People's Republic of China was founded in 1949.
</P>
<P>
This notion was emphasized at the 6th session of the Chinese
Christianity Foundation early this year, Shi said, and the CPC's
policies on religion have brought closer ties between religious
people, the state, and society, and that religion "has found its
location in the country's development." 
</P>
</TEXT>
