<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 26 (Xinhua) -- China's first organic peroxide
joint venture opened today in Tianjin, an industrial and port city
in north China.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin Akzo Nobel Peroxide Co. was launched by Tianjin
Chemical Industry Corporation, the Netherlands' Akzo Nobel, and a
Japanese partner, Kayaku Corporation, at a cost of ten million US
dollars. The three hold a 25-percent, 65-percent, and 10-percent
stake, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The company will produce 2,000 tons of organic peroxides
annually for use in producing polymers, for solidification of
unsaturated polyesters, and for manufacturing coatings.
</P>
<P>
Akzo Nobel is one of the world's major companies for producing
healthcare medicines, coating materials, chemical goods, and
fiber. It already has six regional offices, seven joint ventures,
two corporations, and one wholly-funded company in China. 
