<HEADLINE> HK to Build Science, Technology Corridor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 26 (Xinhua) -- A North-South Corridor of
Science and Technology will be built along the Hong Kong section
of the Kowloon-Guangdong Railway linking the city with neighboring
Guangdong Province, a Hong Kong government official said today.
</P>
<P>
Leung Po-wing, Secretary for Planning, Environment and Lands,
explained that it will be part of his agency's efforts to ease the
pressure from the sustained development a booming service industry
on the already congested downtown area.
</P>
<P>
The service industry has been flourishing in Hong Kong since
the beginning of the 1980s, promoting the adjustment of the
region's economic structure, he said.
</P>
<P>
Yet this has also resulted in shortages of office and
residential buildings in the downtown area, Leung added.
</P>
<P>
To ease the congestion in the old city area, he noted, the
government plans to build more facilities along the city's
north-south traffic trunk, and new business service centers at the
junctions of railways and highways.
</P>
<P>
"Our goal is to build Hong Kong into a commercial, economic and
high-tech service center with a high added value, as well as a
first-rate convention and exhibition center," said Leung.
</P>
<P>
He noted the government will encourage private businesses to
invest in such projects, while the public sector will also provide
support.  
</P>
