<HEADLINE> Tibet Destroys Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Tibetan police today destroyed 105
kg of marijuana, a kilogram of heroin, and 119 opium bulbs that
were confiscated recently here in the capital of the autonomous
region.
</P>
<P>
The vast and sparsely populated Tibet has been chosen by
international drug dealers as a convenient transit area going to
nearby countries.
</P>
<P>
Local police and customs officers have dealt with many
drug-related cases since 1994. Xigaze police seized 120 chunks of
marijuana at a mountain pass at one border area in May, the
largest amount ever seized at one time.
</P>
<P>
Tibet for a long time was proud to be drug-free. But the
penetration by international drug cartels in recent years has
brought an increasing number of drug-related crimes in the
region. Local officials have vowed to crack down on drugs to keep
them away from the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
