<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuomintang Revolutionary Committee Hails Impending Hong Kong Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The Revolutionary Committee of the
Chinese Kuomintang (RCCK), one of China's eight non-communist
parties, will take an active part in the country's reunification
cause as Hong Kong's return nears, its Chairwoman He Luli said
here today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the 19th meeting of the Standing Committee of the
Eighth Central Committee of the RCCK, she said that, in addition
to supporting the central government's "One country, two systems"
policy and the Basic Law of Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region, the committee will continue to fight against any "One
China, one Taiwan," "Two Chinas," or "An Independent Taiwan"
conspiracy that aims to hinder reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
She noted that China's "One country, two systems" policy, which
contributed a lot to the handover of Hong Kong, will continue to
play a key role in solving the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
The RCCK will adhere to the eight-point proposal raised by
Chinese President Jiang Zemin on the Taiwan issue, she added.
</P>
<P>
The participants also discussed the organizing work of the
RCCK, and arrangements for its 50th anniversary celebrations later
this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
