<HEADLINE> Shanghai Pushing Name-Brand Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai branch of the
Industrial and Commercial Bank of China today granted 390 million
yuan in loans to 27 local industrial enterprises to help them get
a greater market share for their name-brand products.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises are producing foodstuff, chemicals for daily
use, and household appliances.
</P>
<P>
The name-brand products include "Big Rabbit" candies, "White
Cat" laundry powder, "Zhonghua" pencils and toothpaste, "Double
Happiness" Ping-Pong equipment, "Hero" pens, and "Daffodil"
washing machines.
</P>
