<HEADLINE> Over 2,119 Kg of Narcotic Drugs Burned in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities today set
ablaze over 2,119 kilograms of narcotic drugs in Kyaington,
eastern Shan state of the country, to mark the International Day
Against Drug Abuse and Trafficking.
</P>
<P>
The destroyed narcotic drugs, which were seized from five
refineries, included 2,010.72 kilograms of opium, 4.41 kilograms
of heroin, 49.3 kilograms of morphine, 733,542 tablets of
stimulant drugs and a large number of chemical substances.
</P>
<P>
Members of foreign diplomatic Corps, United Nations
representatives, local and foreign news media and various
anti-narcotic agency representatives witnessed the destruction of
the seized narcotic drugs.
</P>
<P>
A senior drug control official said earlier today that Myanmar
destroyed 24 heroin refineries and confiscated a total of 5,534.54
kilograms of narcotic drugs in the country since the beginning of
1996 up to the first quarter of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar's ceremonial destruction of narcotic drugs started from
1990 and up to now, over 18,411 kilograms, including 1,961
kilograms of heroin and 11,912 kilograms of opium, have been
burned.  
</P>
</TEXT>
