<HEADLINE> CPPCC Holds Meeting on Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) held a
meeting here today to greet Hong Kong's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was presided over by Vice-chairman Ye Xuanping of
the CPPCC National Committee.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, chairman of the CPPCC National Committee, was
present, as was Wu Xueqian, another vice-chairman, who said that
China's resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong
reflected the aspirations of the entire Chinese people, including
the people living in Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Wu attributed the return to the application of the great
concept of Deng Xiaoping's "One country, two systems" and said he
considers it a guarantee for the stable transition and smooth
return of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"The concept reflects Deng's broad thinking as a patriot and
his foresight and sagacity as a statesman," Wu said, noting that
"Deng's theory represents the interests and desire of all the
Chinese nationalities and shows a practical approach that takes
Hong Kong's history and reality into consideration.
</P>
<P>
He said that the successful return of Hong Kong will erase all
traces of 150 years of disgrace, and will mark a big step towards
China's peaceful reunification.
</P>
<P>
Among those present at the meeting were other vice-chairmen of
the CPPCC National Committee. 
</P>
