<HEADLINE> HK Restaurants Receipts, Purchases on Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The value of total receipts for
the restaurants sector in the first quarter of 1997, estimated at
14.8 billion HK dollars (1.9 billion US dollars), rose nine
percent over the same quarter in 1996, according to the Census and
Statistics Department.
</P>
<P>
The value of total purchases of restaurants increased by seven
percent to 5.2 billion HK dollars (670 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Compared with a year ago, total receipts of Chinese restaurants
and fast food shops had the most rapid growth, both showing an
upsurge of 11 percent in value terms. In volume terms, they rose
by eight percent and six percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The total receipts of bars also went up, by 10 percent in value
and four percent in volume.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the preceding quarter, total receipts for the
restaurants sector in the first quarter of 1997 increased by one
percent in value, but remained virtually unchanged in volume.
</P>
</TEXT>
