population but analysis of various socio-economic activities has
revealed that women participation level is very low and
disparities do not correspondent with the population ratios.
</P>
<P>
"More men are in management and technical jobs and women are
relegated to low paying jobs and lower levels of the informal
sector," Zimba said, at present women are finding it difficult to
take up decision making roles both personally and at institution
levels because of lack of encouragement.
</P>
<P>
