<HEADLINE> Guangzhou, HK Co-operate to Save Sick Air Hostess </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Baiyun Airport in the city of
Guangzhou co-operated with Hong Kong this afternoon in an
emergency landing of a Boeing 737 that had an air hostess on board
who was in immediate need of medical assistance.
</P>
<P>
Soon after the Air China plane took off from Hong Kong's Kai
Tak Airport at noon, the air hostess started bleeding profusely
and needed emergency treatment.
</P>
<P>
The pilot requested assistance from air traffic control in Hong
Kong and they decided to land at Baiyun in nearby Guangzhou in
Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The Central-South China Air Traffic Control Center relayed
instructions from the airport, which had just been hit by a
thunderstorm, delaying a large number of flights.
</P>
<P>
Ground support at the airport were prepared for the landing and
took the sick air hostess to a nearby hospital for treatment.
</P>
</TEXT>
