<HEADLINE> Colombia's Party Leader Optimistic About Hong Kong's Future </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong will maintain
its political stability and economic prosperity after its return
to China, a senior Colombian political leader said today.
</P>
<P>
"The fears ... that there would be a collision between two
ideological concepts with economic repercussions were overrated,"
Co-President of Colombia's ruling National Liberal Party Emilio
Lebolo Castellanos told Xinhua in an exclusive interview at the
party's headquarters.
</P>
<P>
He said the return of Hong Kong on July 1 is of significant
importance and will help put China in the ranks of leading
economic powers in the future world.
</P>
<P>
Lebolo Castellanos added he believes that the concept of "one
country, two systems" applied by the Chinese government to solve
the Hong Kong issue is to bring about a revaluation of economic
process among different ideologies.
</P>
<P>
He said that the "one country, two systems" principle put
forward by the late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping will provide
experience to other countries for resolving similar issues.
</P>
<P>
"We no longer have to believe that two countries, with
different ideological conceptions, must confront each other. We
have to learn how to think about living together," he added.
</P>
<P>
"We are friends of the People's Republic of China. We have
followed closely, with great concern and admiration at the same
time, the whole historical process that China is experiencing," he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
