<HEADLINE> HK Return to Promote Economic Exchange with Other Parts of China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- About 30 Chinese experts said
here today that the return of Hong Kong to the motherland will
promote economic exchanges and cooperation between the island and
inland areas of China.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a seminar on cooperative relations between Hong
Kong and the inland areas, They agreed that Hong Kong and the
inland areas will enter a more prosperous era after July 1 in
their economic cooperation, and that they foresee more
advantageous exchanges between them.
</P>
<P>
Imports and exports and trade will continue to develop, and the
central-western area of China will become an investment hotspot
for Hong Kong businessmen.
</P>
<P>
