<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Investment Funds to Have Vast Room for Expansion in Post- </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The upcoming return of Hong Kong
to China on July 1 will open a tremendous opportunity for Hong
Kong's investment funds to achieve further development, local
professionals said.
</P>
<P>
In a recent interview with the local media, Andrew Lo, chairman
of the Hong Kong Investment Funds Association, said the fund
sector is generally optimistic about the prospects of Hong Kong's
financial market.
</P>
<P>
"After Hong Kong returns to China, the development of funds in
the country's interior areas will create many opportunities for
fund companies based in Hong Kong," Lo was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
He explained that the funds have much room for development in
China's interior areas, where 1.2 billion people have a huge
savings deposit but there are not enough channels of investment.
</P>
<P>
"Foreign-funded fund companies in Hong Kong will benefit a
great deal once a law concerning fund management is adopted in the
interior areas," he noted.
</P>
<P>
An important way of investment in the financial market, the
funds are mainly composed of stocks, the monetary market, bonds
and other categories. There are now 1,000 funds with government
recognition in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1986, the Hong Kong Investment Funds Association is
a professional body representing the local fund management sector.
It now has 45 member companies, which manage funds of various
kinds worth a total of 100 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
As a part of the local financial system, Lo said, the fund
sector has contributed greatly to Hong Kong's current status as an
international financial center.
</P>
<P>
"Since a large proportion of the capital under the management
of local fund companies comes from overseas, Hong Kong's fund
management is playing a vital role in the financial and economic
circle of the entire Asia-Pacific region," he explained.
</P>
<P>
He said that the funds can exert two significant effects on the
economy, namely, stabilizing the market, and increasing efficiency
in the use of capital.
</P>
<P>
"With a thriving funds market, China's interior areas will
enjoy a more stable economic environment and rely less on the
foreign capital," he claimed.
</P>
<P>
He added that his association is planning to launch two
short-term training programs each year, in an effort to help the
interior areas to foster a team of skilled personnel in fund
management.
</P>
<P>
In the years ahead, he predicted, all Hong Kong fund companies
would set up research centers in China's interior areas, and some
companies of larger sizes would also expand their business to the
interior area.
</P>
<P>
"I also believe that with its unique advantages, Hong Kong will
retain its status as the regional headquarters for fund
companies," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970626.0153 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Increases Garments, Textiles Exports to EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's exports of garments and
textiles to the European Union (EU) market reached a record high
of 157 million U.S. dollars in the first five months of 1997, up
42 percent over the same period of last year, local reports said
today.
</P>
<P>
The exports will raise the value of the country's export to the
EU to 220 million dollars in the first half of this year, an
increase of 50 percent over the 1996 figure.
</P>
<P>
Germany, Vietnam's largest garments and textiles customer,
imported 75 million dollars in the first five months, followed by
France's 20 million dollars and the Netherlands' 17.8 million
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The exports were achieved mainly by 52 of the country's 252
enterprises licensed to directly export garments and textiles to
the EU, each posting an export turnover of more than one million
dollars. 
</P>
