<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Investment Expands In East China's Port City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong businessmen had invested
a total of nearly 2.3 billion US dollars in east China's port city
of Nantong by mid-June this year, and had established 1,457
factories, official statistics show.
</P>
<P>
The investments concentrate on light industry, textile,
chemical industry, electronics and real estate, and most of the
businesses operate well, officials say.
</P>
<P>
In the city's economic and technological development zone, the
number of Hong Kong-backed firms accounts for about one third of
the total.
</P>
<P>
Nantong is one of China's first 14 coastal open cities. Jiangsu
province's first overseas-financed enterprise was set up in the
city, according to Zhao Hongzhang, director of the City Commission
of Foreign Trade and Economic Co-operation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
