<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar closed
mostly steady amid caution ahead of the Reserve Bank of Australia
(RBA) gathering.
</P>
<P>
The local unit ended at 75.06 US cents, from Wednesday's close
at 75.11 US cents. During the session it traded between 75 US
cents and 75.15 US cents.
</P>
<P>
A Chase Manhatten foreign exchange dealer said there were
varying schools of thought on the short term outlook for official
interest rates.
</P>
<P>
Traders said doubts continue in the market as to whether or not
RBA will ease policy following its board meeting next Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A MMS Standard &AMP; Poor's survey of economists found 58 percent
of financial market economists in Sydney expect the Reserve Bank
will ease rates by the end of the third quarter, while 40 percent
expect steady rates and one percent expect higher rates.
</P>
<P>
On the crosses, the Australian dollar ended at 85.48 Japanese
yen, from 85.21 yen, and at 1.2961 German marks from 1.2911 marks.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
