<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central China Province Combats Drug-Related Crimes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Hunan Province
has solved 3,719 drug-related cases as part of an anti-drug
campaign launched since the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
By the end of May, local police in the province had seized a
total of 7.93 kgs of heroin, 8.93 kg of opium, and about 1,069 kgs
of other drugs.
</P>
<P>
About 3,854 people have been charged in connection with
drug-related crimes, and 60 drug traffickers have been arrested,
with 2,539 addicts sentenced to attend drug rehabilitation
programs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
