<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Decline Sharply on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined sharply on
the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index fell by 34.06 points to close below the 2000-point level at
1,989.8 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume stood at 127.01 million units, worth
385.98 million Singapore dollars (about 269.92 million US
dollars). declines overwhelmed advances by 222 to 95, while 306
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Van Der Horst was again the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 17.46 million units. It was followed by
Multi Purpose which had 5.21 million shares traded. Excel was next
with 4.79 million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 led the gainers of
the day as it rose by 60 cents to finish at 24 Singapore dollars.
Van Der Warrant 98 increased by 34 cents to end at 2.15 Singapore
dollars, while Sea View closed 30 cents higher at 11.2 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Bukit Sambawang and Roth M 200 shared the top
spot on the loser's list as each of them declined by 1.2 dollars
to close at 26.8 and 14 Singapore dollars respectively. The
Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign fell by 80 cents to finish
at 28.3 Singapore dollars and GE Life ended 70 cents lower at 16.5
Singapore dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
