<HEADLINE> Nepal's 12th Session of Parliament Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The 12th session of the
parliament of Nepal opens here today, with the passage of national
budget for the fiscal year 1997-98 on its top agenda.
</P>
<P>
Also awaiting to be voted during this session are an ordinance
concerning local bodies and various important bills, said the
Ministry of Parliamentary Affairs (MPA).
</P>
<P>
Since the 11th session of the parliament was occupied mainly by
confidence motions, not a single bill was passed.
</P>
<P>
As a result, a total of 37 bills have been registered with the
MPA to be presented to the lower house during the 12th session.
</P>
<P>
During this session, balloting will also be held to elect 12
upper house members, which will take place Friday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
