<HEADLINE> hkhk-HK Garment Industry Turns to Market in Interior Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This will be the ninth consecutive year for TDC to organize
local business people to attend the annual fair, which is cited as
an "ideal springboard" to enter into the potentially-huge garment
market in northeast China.
As local garment industry turns to the market in the interior
area,
Hong Kong is planning and making active preparations to increase
the presence of its textile industry at the market in the
interior.
Breakdowns show that the retail sales of Liaoning, one of the
three northeastern provinces, alone reached 112.6 billion yuan in
1994, ranking the fourth place nationally.
</P>
<P>
Last year, 69 Hong Kong companies attending the fair struck a
total of orders worth 182 million HK dollars and sold two million
HK dollars worth of goods at the fair site, and received orders
worth 99.8 million HK dollars during business talks, according to
TDC figures.
</P>
<P>
With rapid rise in people's living standards, many brand-name
garments made in Hong Kong, such as "Playboy", "Crocodile",
"Jeanwest" and "Puma" have been selling well in many parts of
China.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the Jeanwest International (HK) disclosed the
company has already opened more than 300 chain stores in some 20
provinces and municipalities, all of which have made profits.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the company plans to increase the number of its
outlets to 380 at the end of this year, and proceed to 500 in late
1998 and to 1000 in the year 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
