<HEADLINE> China Hopes Sino-Russian Ties Continue to Grow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman
Cui Tiankai said today China values its strategic and cooperative
partnership with Russia, hoping to work with Russia to further the
bilateral ties in various areas.
</P>
<P>
Cui told a routine press briefing here that the past several
years have witnessed stable growth of the Sino-Russian relations,
and, in particular, President Jiang Zemin's successful visit to
Russia this April "delivered new progress in the strategic and
cooperative partnership between the two countries."
</P>
<P>
Russian Prime Minister Victor Chernomyrdin, who starts an
official visit to China today, will have a wide-ranging and
profound exchange of views on various questions with his Chinese
counterpart Premier Li Peng, including the one concerning bringing
the bilateral trade volume to 20 billion US dollars at the end of
the century, a goal set at their first meeting last December.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin arrived in Shenzhen, a special economic zone in
South China, this morning to start his three-day official visit to
China. It will be the second time the prime ministers of both
countries will hold talks since China and Russia set up a schedule
of regular meetings between the leaders last December.
</P>
<P>
"The trade and economic cooperation between China and Russia is
far from what the strategic and cooperative partnership calls
for," Cui said.
</P>
<P>
However, he added, China is optimistic about the realization of
the above goal, because the economies of the two countries are
strongly complementary and the economic cooperation has great
potentials.
</P>
<P>
According to Cui, the two sides will sign some cooperation
agreements during Chernomyrdin's visit to China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
