<HEADLINE> Book Series Published to Display Mongolian Literature </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HUHHOT, June 26 (Xinhua) -- China recently published a series
of books to showcase the literary achievements of the Mongolian
people since the era of Genghis Khan (1162-1227).
</P>
<P>
The collection, with more than 900,000 Chinese characters,
includes full-length novels, prose and poetry.
</P>
<P>
Literary critics believe the series will greatly benefit the
study of Mongolian literature, history and folklore.
</P>
<P>
Bu He, vice-chairman of the National People's Congress Standing
Committee, has called for efforts to publish more literary works
to reflect the life of minority groups in the country.
</P>
<P>
China has 56 ethnic groups.  
