<HEADLINE> More Overseas Investment Attracted to Farming Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Overseas investment in the
agricultural sector of Haikou, capital of south China's island
province of Hainan, has grown significantly since the start of
this year, official figures show.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investors have set up 25 enterprises specializing in
agricultural development and processing agricultural produce and
sideline products, with investment totalling more than 100 million
US dollars, about 41 percent of all overseas investment in the
provincial capital so far this year.
</P>
<P>
The fact that the farming sector is now able to claim one of
the highest rates of profit for per unit of cost is a major reason
for overseas investors' increasing interest in agriculture,
experts say.
</P>
<P>
They also note that the farming sector is protected and
supported by the government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
