<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Stock Markets Set Daily Listing Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 26 (Xinhua) -- A record for new listings on
China's stock markets has been set after ten companies put out a
total of 480 million new shares today on the Shanghai and Shenzhen
exchanges.
</P>
<P>
The amount far surpassed the former record of 170 million
shares, which were listed by 11 companies on February 24, 1994.
</P>
<P>
One of the companies listed 90 million shares, while the
smallest listing involved 13 million.
</P>
<P>
Most of the newly listings were made by manufacturers of
computers, motorcycles, and machinery products. Three of them
were listed in the Shanghai Stock Exchange, while the other seven
featured on the Shenzhen Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
Market experts say the block listing is a clear indication that
the authorities are determined to check market speculation by
accelerating efforts to list companies. It is one action aimed at
putting the financial market on an acceptable path of development.
</P>
<P>
Six more companies are due to list a total of 280 million
shares on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
