<DOCNO> XIE19970626.0184 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua Article on HK Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Xinhua News Agency today published
a 6,000-word article by its correspondents hailing the impending
Hong Kong handover as a symbol of China's entry into a new era
marked by reunification and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
The first part of the text, subtitled "150 Years of Disgrace Is
to be Erased," says Hong Kong's history from its cession to return
demonstrates that socialism is the only road of China to national
reunification and prosperity, and that the Chinese Communist Party
is worthy of the title of national hero for its efforts toward
this end
</P>
<P>
The article reviews Chinese modern history, the Opium Wars in
particular, saying that British colonialists' canons and warships
led to the signing of three humiliating treaties which took away
more than 1,000 square kilometers of Chinese territory, including
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"Emperor Daoguang of the Qing Dynasty had not the slightest
idea of Britain's geographic location, even after China's
disastrous defeat in the Opium Wars," the article pointed
out. "With such ignorance and self-isolation, how can national
sovereignty be defended and national dignity be preserved?"
</P>
<P>
The article says that imperialists and colonialists could
invade and occupy part of China's territory, but could never
conquer its patriotic spirit.
</P>
<P>
Recalling the century-long struggle of the Chinese people
against imperialism and colonialism, the article says that only
when the banner of patriotism is upheld by the Communist Party of
China, which combines the simple aspiration for national salvation
with the truth of Marxist theory, could the Chinese nation find the
right path to national reunification and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
It was late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping who proclaimed to the
world that China would resume the exercise of sovereignty over
Hong Kong, and it is the reform and opening-up and growing
economic strength of socialist China that made this possible, the
article says.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese communists are the most steadfast and thorough
patriots and are worthy of the title of national hero.
</P>
<P>
"July 1: a sacred and meaningful date. It is not just a
coincidence that the date marks the birth of a great party and
also the termination of a humiliating past."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970626.0185 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua Article on HK Return (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The second part of the article points out that the formulation
of the "one country, two systems" concept is a reflection of the
selflessness and breadth of vision as well as steadfastness and
flexibility of the Chinese Communist Party and the Chinese
government. The great concept led to the solution of a difficult
question left over from the past.
</P>
<P>
The Communist Party of China is of the view that that two
different social systems can seek common ground while reserving
their differences for the sake of fundamental interest of the
country and the nation.
</P>
<P>
The article says the first generation of the Party's leadership
was farsighted enough to see that the reunification of the
motherland could be achieved peacefully. With that vision, the
second generation formed the great concept of "one country, two
systems," and the third generation has put it into practice.
</P>
<P>
The present Party leadership opened a new chapter in Chinese
history by doing a great deal of work for the return of Hong Kong
to the motherland and for its long-term stability and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
According to the article, "Hong Kong compatriots will end their
life under colonialism, go back to the embrace of their motherland
and become for the first time masters of their own destiny."
</P>
<P>
It offers the assurance that nothing will change the principle
of "one country, two systems."
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's retaining of the capitalist system and capitalist
lifestyle for 50 years was proposed by Deng Xiaoping. As long as
the Party sticks to its basic lines set by Deng, "there will be no
change, also no reason to make any change, to the principle on
Hong Kong."
</P>
<P>
The Party and central government will employ every possible
means to ensure Hong Kong's high degree of autonomy guaranteed in
the Basic Law, notes the article.
</P>
<P>
The return of Hong Kong strengthens the unity of the Chinese
nation. More and more Hong Kong people become aware that their
destiny is closely linked with that of their motherland."
</P>
<P>
The article reiterates the idea of ultimate reunification
between the mainland and Taiwan and predicts that a successful
experimentation of the "one country, two systems" concept in Hong
Kong will have a profound influence on Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
"The reunification and prosperity of the motherland is the
common aspiration of the Chinese nation. Who will refuse to be a
member of a big Chinese family when a strong China emerges on the
horizon in the 21st century?" the article quotes a professor from
Taiwan as saying.
</P>
<P>
The article points out that the third generation of the Party's
leadership is fully aware that the return of Hong Kong is just the
first step toward the grand goal of reunification, and the smooth
implementation of the principle of "one country, two systems" will
greatly boost that prospect.
</P>
<P>
"To realize the reunification of the country is the national
aspiration. If the reunification will not come about in one
hundred years, it will in one thousand years," the article
concludes, quoting Deng Xiaoping. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
