<HEADLINE> Manila to Host ASEAN Investment Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Senior officials from the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) will gather here on
July 1 to discuss how to attract more foreign direct investments
and promote intra-country investments in the region.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine Department of Trade and Industry said today in a
statement that the senior officials from ASEAN investment
promotion agencies will work hard to formulate a framework aimed
at establishing a regional investment area for the entire ASEAN
market.
</P>
<P>
They will outline the direction for regional investment
cooperation to hasten ASEAN's growth as a major economic bloc not
only in Asia but also in the world, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The strategies to be tackled at the meeting include technology
and information sharing, joint undertaking of investment promotion
activities and establishing of an ASEAN technology bank and an
ASEAN investment club.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the officials will also look at the results
of previous economic fora by their economic ministers.
</P>
<P>
At present, ASEAN groups Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, the
Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam. It will admit
Cambodia, Laos and Myanmar next month.  
</P>
