<DOCNO> XIE19970626.0192 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Bank Sets up Special Committee for Risk Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The Agricultural Bank of China
(ABC) has set up an auditing and supervision committee in an
effort to improve internal control, and prevent and ward off
financial risks.
</P>
<P>
The committee is the first of its kind established by a
state-owned Chinese bank and is ABC's third specialized committee
following two others for overseeing asset-to-liability management
and credit extension.
</P>
<P>
Analysts say that China's commercial banks have been weak at
standardizing their operations, exercising self-restraint and
conducting internal management, which is considered as factors
prone to risks at some financial institutions.
</P>
<P>
ABC's auditing and supervision committee, which is established
on the headquarters' level, will do research and formulate principles
and policies for business operation and risk prevention, draw
annual objectives and medium and long-term plan for risk
examination and evaluation, make decisions of economic punishment
against those accountable for major economic cases and rule
violations, and propose for criminal punishment when necessary.
</P>
<P>
ABC is one of China's big-four state-owned commercial
banks. The other three are the Industrial and Commercial Bank of
China, the Bank of China, and the China Construction Bank.
</P>
<P>
As China moves to a market economy and accelerates its pace to
turn its banks into real economic entities, risk control has
become overwhelmingly urgent and important. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970626.0193 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Government's Size Doubled in 26 Years: WB </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The government size of Bangladesh
has doubled since the country won independence in 1971, according
to a World Bank report released here today.
</P>
<P>
The World Development Report 1997 said that the number of
ministries in Bangladesh increased from 21 to 35 in the past 26
years, and between 1990 and 1994 the number of departments and
directorates rose from 109 to 221.
</P>
<P>
Public sector employment increased from 450,000 to an almost
one million in 1992, registering an annual increase of 3.6
percent, compared with the population growth of 2.5 percent each
year during the same period.
</P>
<P>
The report said the new ministries, divisions and departments
were created in part to meet emerging needs such as environmental
protection and women's issues.
</P>
<P>
"But the state has also spread its wings into commercial
activities," said the report, adding growth has often been
stimulated by political considerations.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the increase in ministries allowed new
ministerial positions to be handed out to more intra-party groups
and, of course, created more low level jobs to be dispensed.
</P>
<P>
Aside from its budgetary effects, this expansion has stretched
implementation capacity, compounded coordination problems, and
made regulation more intrusive, the report said.
</P>
<P>
World Bank Resident Mission Chief Pierre Landel-Mils welcomed
the formation of an Administrative Reform Commission with the
capacity of a cabinet minister, saying the appointment sends the
"key signal that it's an important area."
</P>
<P>
Landel-Mills hoped that the commission would be thinking in a
"radical way" for reforming the administration. But, he noted that
it would not be an easy task and called for collective efforts in
this respect.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
