<HEADLINE> Western Uganda Under Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Western Uganda district of
Bundibugyo was under control by the government troops, "The New
Vision" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Allied Democratic Forces (ADF) group acting in Bundibugyo
district have been compressed to a mountain area near
Uganda-Congo border.
</P>
<P>
But military sources said ADF sent the group to Bundibugyo to
develop a reliable source for food.
</P>
<P>
Between 200 and 300 ADF rebels are still in the district,
according to local paper.
</P>
<P>
Ismael Mayanjia, a captured ADF rebel, told the newspaper that
the rebel detachment harassing the district in recent ten days
has 250 members.
</P>
<P>
Mayanjia said ADF lured recruits by promising big cash prizes,
huge houses and vehicles. Mayanjia was a fish monger and brick
maker before he joined ADF ranks in February last year.
</P>
<P>
Four government soldiers, ten rebels and 11 civilians were
killed in separate clashes, and three rebels were captured in the
district Tuesday, State Minister for Defense Amama Mbabazi said
yesterday.
</P>
<P>
ADF is a rebel group acting in the west and has hundreds of
fighters in its ranks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
