<HEADLINE> hkhk - Posters on HK's Handover Becomes Big Attraction for Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 26 (Xinhua) -- One of the hottest selling
souvenirs on Hong Kong's handover is the official set of 12,
top-quality posters produced by the government to highlight the
many overseas visitors.
</P>
<P>
On display at the Press and Broadcast Center in the Hong Kong
Convention and Exhibition Center, they have quickly attracted the
attention of media staff from around the world here to cover the
historic event.
</P>
<P>
Staff at the center say the sets of posters have been snapped
up, particularly by television broadcasters who are using them as
colorful backgrounds for some of their programs.
</P>
<P>
They are also big sellers for the public who are buying them at
20 HK dollars each from the Government Publications Center in
Admiralty.
</P>
<P>
Staff at the Center say there has been a big demand for the
limited edition posters which are seen as one of the cheapest and
most colorful mementos of Hong Kong at this turning point in its
history. Because of the demand, they are expected to be sold out
soon.
</P>
<P>
The posters feature the words of Hong Kong in Chinese and
English as well as the official logo for the 1997 Handover events,
the Lantau Link, the Po Lin Buddha, a bustling street scene,
school children at play, a Cantonese opera, the Kwai Chung
container terminal and a building draped in scaffolding. 
