<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Party Members Told to Stand Ahead of Times, Play Exemplary Role </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Members of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) should always "stand ahead of the times and fully play
a pioneering and exemplary role," said a senior Chinese Party official.
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, made the call in a speech
delivered on June 20 at a forum organized to mark the 76th
anniversary of the founding of CPC.
</P>
<P>
The speech was published in full length in today's "People's
Daily", the leading national newspaper.
</P>
<P>
The period between now and the year 2010 is an important one as
China transits from the second stage to the third on its way to
fulfill its strategic goal of socialist modernization.
</P>
<P>
"A historical task that lays in front of the whole party is to
hold high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping's theory of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics, seize every opportunities,
and push forward reform, opening-up and modernization drive to a
new era," said the senior Chinese party leader.
</P>
<P>
The tasks under new situations are very urgent, so it is
necessary to improve the quality of party members and to bring their
pioneering and exemplary role into full play, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
He reminded that as China's reform and opening-up drive proceed
in depth and socialist market economic mechanisms are being
established in more and more places, party members are now
confronted with an environment and conditions quite different from
those of the past time. Under the new circumstances, party memembers
are required to maintain their progressive character and to play
an exemplary role.
</P>
<P>
Hu, also a member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central
Committee, warned that now a small number of party members have
not survived the tests of new historic changes and lost their
progressive character, or even degenerated so far as to go against
the party and the people.
</P>
<P>
It is necessary to brave the problems and to put improvement of
party members top on the work agenda, said Hu.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese party leader also urged party members to use their
acts to preserve their progressive character, stand in the
forefront of the historic times and to play a pioneering and
exemplary role.
</P>
<P>
While urging party members to keep a close link with the broad
masses of the people and be concerned with the weal and woe of the
people, Hu also called on them to voluntarily resist corrosive
influence of decadent ideology of the exploiting classes and to take
the lead in practicing and publicizing socialist ethics and
healthy habits.
</P>
<P>
He also urged party organizations at various levels to
strengthen education and management on party members and create
conditions for them to fully play a pioneering and exemplary
role.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970626.0204 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
