<HEADLINE> Philippines' San Miguel to Merge 2 Subsidiaries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- San Miguel Corporation announced
here today that it will merge San Miguel Properties Philippines,
Inc. (SMPPI) with Monterey Farms Corporation (MFC) to strengthen
its real estate business.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here, the Philippine corporation said
that as its Monterey Farms Corporation is a listed company and
will be the surviving entity, the merger will provide San Miguel's
real estate business with a vehicle to access the equity capital
market in the future to finance its re-development projects.
</P>
<P>
San Miguel said that in preparation for the merger, which is
expected to be completed within three to four months, Monterey
will spin off its meat business, including all operating assets
and liabilities, into a separate company to be known as Monterey
Foods Corporation.
</P>
<P>
The merged company will focus solely on real estate and have
assets valued at about 16.4 billion pesos (625 million U.S.
dollars), representing 15.2 billion (580 million dollars) from
SMPPI and 1.2 billion pesos (45 million dollars) from Monterey,
San Miguel said.
</P>
<P>
It said that the merger will consolidate its landholdings with
re-development potential into a single structure.  
</P>
