<HEADLINE> More Foreign Airlines Operating in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai has established
scheduled air links with 22 foreign airlines in 17 countries and
regions, making the city the second busiest air hub in China after
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
As many as 230 flights by foreign carriers are operated in and
out of Shanghai's Hongqiao International Airport every week, and
more than 1.44 million passengers and 89,000 tons of cargo were
transported by foreign airliners last year, up by 89 percent and
over 100 percent respectively than the year before.
</P>
<P>
Most developed countries and regions now offer air services to
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Cargo and passenger volume handled at Hongqiao airport has
steadily increased in recent years, making it one of the biggest
air freight centers in the country.
</P>
<P>
The city is expected to start up more foreign air links when
construction of Shanghai Pudong International Airport is
completed. 
</P>
