<DOCNO> XIE19970626.0224 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> hkhk -Hong Kong-related Data (14):Preparatory Committee for HKSAR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The Preparatory Committee for
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) is a working
body empowered by the National People Congress (NPC).
</P>
<P>
Its main task is to make preparations for the establishment of
the first government, legislature and other organs of the HKSAR in
accordance with the Basic Law and relevant decisions of the NPC.
</P>
<P>
The Decision of the NPC on the Methods for the Formation of the
First Government and Legislative Council of the HKSAR adopted by
the Third Session of the Seventh NPC on April 4, 1990, stipulated
that the NPC will set up a Preparatory Committee for the HKSAR
within 1996, which will take charge of matters concerning the
preparations for the establishment of the HKSAR and decide in
accordance with this Decision on the specific methods for the
formation of the first Government and Legislative Council.
</P>
<P>
The Preparatory Committee was set up in January 1996 with 150
members and with Vice Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen as
its chairman. Among the 150 committee members, 56, or about 37
percent, are from the inland area, and 94, or 63 percent, are from
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
So far, the committee has held nine plenary meetings and 40
panel meetings, and accomplished the following seven jobs:
</P>
<P>
-- Forming a Selection Committee consisting of 400 permanent
residents of Hong Kong;
</P>
<P>
-- Electing the first Chief Executive of the HKSAR;
</P>
<P>
-- Electing the 60-member Provisional Legislative Council;
</P>
<P>
-- Raising a proposal after systematic studies that most of
Hong Kong's existing laws should be retained intact;
</P>
<P>
-- Doing research and raising proposals on a series of
important economic issues concerning the smooth transfer of Hong
Kong's political power, such as the compilation of the budget for
97/98 fiscal year, monetary stability, transfer of government
assets, and large-scale infrastructure projects;
</P>
<P>
-- Promoting the establishment of the Committee for Celebration
of Hong Kong's Return to the Motherland in Hong Kong to prepare a
variety of non-governmental activities; and
</P>
<P>
-- Formulating the specific method for the formation of the
first legislative council of the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
With the conclusion of the ninth plenary meeting, the
Preparatory Committee has basically completed its task. Since the
Preparatory Committee is a body set up by the NPC, the question of
ceasing its work is up to the Standing Committee of the NPC to
decide.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
