<HEADLINE> New Party to Appear in Romanian Political Arena </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 25 (Xinhua) -- A new party, announced today by
Romanian Senator Teodor Melescanu, is about to appear in Romanian
political arena.
</P>
<P>
Melescanu said he was establishing the party, Alianta Pentru
Romania, or Romanian Union.
</P>
<P>
Melescanu, the former Foreign Minister, who was also the
previous deputy chairman of the former ruling Romanian Socialist
Democratic Party (RSDP), with other important figures of the
party, announced he was quitting at the RSDP's conference last
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
He made the declaration about the new party in a news brief
here today. He said the new party would be center-left, and pursue
the Social Democratic Party of Romania's (SDPR) policy. It would
advocate honest and clean government and oppose corruption.
</P>
<P>
The new party would be in opposition in parliament, but it
would not oppose decisions of the government. The party would
endorse an alliance, mainly with other parties whose policies were
similar to the SDPR.
</P>
<P>
Melescanu said, he would be the leader of the new party. Its
spokesman would be Iosif Boda, who was former party member of the
SDPR, and former Romanian Ambassador to Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
Another Senator, Sergiu Nicolaescu, the famous film director,
announced that he would withdraw from the RSDP at the news
conference, and leave the political arena to return to movies.
</P>
