<HEADLINE> Panamanian FM on Hong Kong's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's return to China is
positive and Hong Kong will continue to be a big window to the
international market, Panamanian Foreign Minister Ricardo Alberto
Arias said today.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks after announcing that Panama will open a
trade office in Hong Kong after the Chinese government resumes the
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong on July 1.
</P>
<P>
Under an agreement signed between Panama and China last year,
Panama would replace its current general consulate office in Hong
Kong with the Economic and Trade Office.
</P>
<P>
The office is a provisional government office, which will have
the faculty to provide consular services apart from continuing to
provide traditional merchant marine services, Alberto Arias said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the office will also be in charge of promoting
trade, economic, cultural and tourist exchanges between Panama and
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the expiration of the trade office in six months,
Panama and China will negotiate and establish a permanent status
of the Panamanian office, the foreign minister added. 
</P>
