<HEADLINE> Nepal to Recruit Sri Lanka's Doctors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 26 (Xinhua) -- A Nepalese parliamentary
delegation is currently in Sri Lanka seeking to recruit doctors
from the country for hospitals in Nepal where there is a shortage
of medical doctors, according to Health Ministry sources today.
</P>
<P>
The delegation which met Deputy Minister of Health and
Indigenous Medicine S. B. Nawinna, had discussions on the details
of the matter and Nepalese students studying medicine at Sri
Lanka's teaching hospitals.
</P>
<P>
Mutual exchange of knowledge of indigenous medicine and the
import of ayurvedic raw materials and herbal plants to Sri Lanka
from Nepal were also discussed, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
At present Sri Lanka has an excess of doctors and is unable to
provide employment for all of them at government hospitals. If the
doctors are to get jobs at Nepalese hospitals, the problem would
be considerably eased for the Sri Lankan government, the sources
pointed out.  
