<HEADLINE> Indonesian Minister Confirms Russian Fighters Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian Foreign Minister Ali
Alatas has confirmed that his country will soon buy Russian-made
fighter jets following the decision to cancel the purchase of nine
F-16 fighters from the United States.
</P>
<P>
"We've made up our mind. But this does not mean we have any
problems with the United States," the minister said here
Wednesday after opening a seminar on Indonesia-Egypt relations,
sources at the seminar disclosed today.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia earlier this month canceled its planned purchase of
nine U.S. F-16s citing "wholly unjustified criticisms" of
Indonesia in the U.S. Congress.
</P>
<P>
Reports said earlier that President Soeharto has assigned
chairman of the national development planning body Ginandjar
Kartasasmita to go to Russia to make the deal.
</P>
<P>
Alatas stressed that Indonesia's refusal to purchase the F-16s
from the United States will not sour relations between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Kartasasmita said last week that the Indonesian Armed Forces
are quite familiar with Russian military equipment. In the 1960s,
the Soviet Union was Indonesia's main supplier of military
equipment, including MIG fighters, wide-bodied Antonovs and tanks.
</P>
<P>
</P>
