<HEADLINE> Guyana's President Meets China's State Councillor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 25 (Xinhua) -- President of Guyana Samuel Hinds
met Chinese State Councillor Song Jian here today.
</P>
<P>
Both President Hinds and State Councillor Song Jian are
attending the 19th Special Session of the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, Song Jian first conveyed the best wishes of
President Jiang Zemin to President Hind. He then expressed China's
willingness to further develop friendly cooperation in all areas
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
President Hinds highly valued the traditional friendship
between the two countries. He noted that Guyana is the first
English-speaking Caribbean country to establish diplomatic
relations with China and that Guyana is now busy preparing for the
celebration of the 25th anniversary of the diplomatic ties.
</P>
