<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia Routs Poland in Euro Basketball Opener </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Olympic runner-up Yugoslavia routed
Poland 104-76 and host Spain downed Ukraine 82-54 in the opening
round of the European basketball championship in Barcelona on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Led by point guard Sasha Danilovic and center Zeljko Rebraca,
Yugoslavia had an easy opening game in the 10-day round-robin
tournament.
</P>
<P>
Danilovic scored 18 points, Rebraca added 19 and forward Dejan
Bodiroga got 16 to take the lead in Group C.
</P>
<P>
In the other Group C game, Italy edged Latvia 85-75.
</P>
<P>
In Group A games played in Girona, Greece overcame Turkey 74-52
and Russia defeated Bosnia 65-55. 
</P>
