<HEADLINE> Spurs Selects Duncan With Top Pick </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The San Antonio Spurs selected
center Tim Duncan with the first pick in the 1997 NBA draft
Wednesday in Charlotte, North Carolina.
</P>
<P>
Dunca, who stands 2.08 meters, has been regarded the best
player in college the last three years. He averaged 20.8 points
and a nation-leading 14.7 rebounds per game last season at Wake
Forest and was the college player of the year.
</P>
<P>
With the second pick, the Philadelphia 76ers chose Utah forward
Keith Van Horn.
</P>
<P>
Boston Celtics, with the third pick, got Colorado guard
Chauncey Billups. 
