<HEADLINE> Panamanian University Students Consume Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Fifty-five percent of
university students in Panama consume analgesics and alcoholic
beverages frequently and one percent consume cocaine, a study
published today shows.
</P>
<P>
The study of 1,095 students from the University of Panama,
Santa Maria la Antigua and the Tech, made by the White Cross and
the Public Magistrate's Office, says that alcohol is the legal
drug consumed by 71.6 percent of the male students and 47.4
percent of the female.
</P>
<P>
Cocaine is the illegal drug used by one percent of the
adolescents, and about 39.8 percent of males and 56.2 of females
use analgesic pills (pain killers).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, about 5,000 people in the country receive treatment
for drug addiction every year in 13 centers.
</P>
<P>
Last Tuesday, the White Cross staged, together with First Lady
Dora de Perez Balladares, a one-week campaign to eradicate and
prevent drug use. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
