<HEADLINE> Milosevic: Yugoslavia Not to Give Up Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslavia will never give up any
land of its Autonomous Province of Kosovo, said Serb President
Slobodan Milosevic on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The position, Milosevic told a mass rally at downtown Pristina,
the Capital of Kosovo, will never change no matter what kind of
pressure Yugoslavia will sustain.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslavia has survived the most serious crisis and now is
working on reforms to accelerate its economic growth and improve
people's living standard, he said.
</P>
<P>
According to a Tanjug news agency report from Kosovo, the Serb
president arrived at Pristina on Wednesday for a one-day
inspection of the city.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav government has rejected the request for
independence by residents in Kosovo, most of whom are ethnic
Albanians. 
</P>
