<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 250 Councillors Murdered in Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- About 250 councillors
and 34 mayors have been assassinated over the past two and half
years in Colombia, said a National Federation of Councils (NFC)
report published today.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, some 500 councillors have left their posts during the
same period following death threats and attempts on their lives by
guerrillas or paramilitary groups, the report was cited by the "El
Nuevo Siglo" newspaper as saying.
</P>
<P>
As for mayors, seven have been assassinated so far this year,
with the northwestern department of Antioquia most affected.
</P>
<P>
From April to May this year, about 20 candidates running for
mayor, councillor, the assembly and congress for the October 26
elections were murdered, while some others were forced to withdraw
after receiving death threats.
</P>
<P>
There is intimidation against public, political and
administrative activities in the municipalities, said NFC
President Alvaro Jimenez Millan.
</P>
<P>
Guerrillas and paramilitary groups have vowed to boycott the
forthcoming elections for mayors, councillors, aldermen and
deputies in election districts where candidates are opposed to
their ideologies and interests. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
