<DOCNO> XIE19970626.0258 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Baggio Says He is Leaving AC Milan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Italian midfielder Roberto Baggio
said on Wednesday he was leaving AC Milan.
</P>
<P>
Interviewed by Italy's RAI television at Venice airport on his
return from a holiday in Argentina, the pony-tailed World Cup star
confirmed his generally-expected departure.
</P>
<P>
Italian newspapers reported earlier this week that coach Fabio
Capello, returning after a season at Real Madrid, had told Baggio
and Yugoslav forward Dejan Savicevic that there would be no place
for them at the club next season.
</P>
<P>
Baggio, who won the league title with Juventus before moving to
Milan and winning the title there the following season in 1996,
also said that no Milan official had contacted him to break the
news, other than Capello.
</P>
<P>
Baggio has been linked in recent weeks to several clubs,
including Napoli and Spain's Barcelona. 
</P>
</TEXT>
