<HEADLINE> China Sweeps Golds at Gymnastics International </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese women gymnasts
cheered the local fans here Wednesday night by sweeping the team
and individual all-around titles at the China-Cup Gymnastics
International Invitational Meet.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team scored the most of 114.212 points for the top
honour, beating Romania and Belarus to second and third spots
respectively with 111.974 and 107.512 points.
</P>
<P>
The women's all-around individual crown was snatched by Meng
Fei of China who accumulated a total of 38.450 points from the
apparatuses. Her teammate Mo Huilan, fifth-placer in Atlanta
all-around competition, finished second on 38.262.
</P>
<P>
The third spot was taken by Alexandra Marinescu of Romania on
38.037.
</P>
<P>
The tournament was exploited by the gymnasts as a tune-up for
the upcoming World Championships slated in September in
Switzerland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
