<HEADLINE> Swiss Gets Stage Win in Swiss Cycling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Swiss Oskar Camenzind rode home
first in the ninth stage of the Tour of Switzerland in Davos on
Wednesday and he is to clash with Christophe Agnolutto for the
overall title in Thursday's final stage.
</P>
<P>
Camenzind, who began the 193-km stage from Wetzikon trailing
Agnolutto by five minutes 14 seconds in the overall standings, cut
three minutes off the Frenchman's lead with his second stage win.
</P>
<P>
The Swiss crossed the finish line 1:06 ahead of second-placed
Germany's Jan Ullrich, who remained third in the overall
rankings. 
