<DOCNO> XIE19970626.0272 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian PM on Relations Between Russia, China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin said there is great potentiality in cooperation
between Russian and China.
</P>
<P>
He said that his upcoming visit to China, scheduled for June
26-28, would add specific contents to the strategic cooperative
partnership between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
At a joint news conference attended by Russian reporters and
those from Xinhua and China's People's Daily, Chernomyrdin said
high-level exchanges between Russia and China have laid basis for
the bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the China visit by Russian President Boris
Yeltsin last year and Chinese President Jiang Zemin's visit to
Russia in April this year are of great importance.
</P>
<P>
During Yeltsin's visit to China, the two leaders agreed to
establish a mechanism of holding regular meetings between the
prime ministers of the two countries, which was started by Chinese
Premier Li Peng's Russia visit in December, 1996.
</P>
<P>
He said this mechanism is aimed at fully expanding bilateral
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Expressing confidence in developing economic and trade
cooperation between Russia and China, he noticed that their
bilateral trade grew by 25 percent last year, a rate much higher
than that between China and its other trade partners.
</P>
<P>
He said Russia and China share increasing interest in the
cooperation in production, investment, joint management, science
and technology, crafts and training.
</P>
<P>
During his visit to China this month, he said, he would meet
Premier Li Peng on cooperation in infrastructure, energy,
transport linking Russia and China, as well as regional
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Chernomyrdin viewed Hong Kong's return to China as
an important historic event for China and the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
He highly praised the concept of "one country, two systems" by
Deng Xiaoping, saying that Hong Kong's return to China is in line
with the basic interest of the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that the Hong Kong industrial and commercial circles
would cooperate with Russia on the basis of mutual benefit and
make contributions to improving economic and trade ties between
Russia and China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
