<HEADLINE> Draws of Women's Volleyball Junior World Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The draws were made on Wednesday
in Gdansk, Poland for the 1997 Women's Junior World Championship
conducted by the International Volleyball Federation.
</P>
<P>
Sixteen teams were bracketed in four groups for the preliminary
rounds which will start on September 5 for three days.
</P>
<P>
The fourth-ranked teams in the preliminary groups will be
eliminated from the 12-member play-off matches.
</P>
<P>
On September 9, eight teams ranked second and third places in
the preliminaries will play the first play-off matches, followed
by the four group leaders.
</P>
<P>
The drawing for the final round will be held on September 9
right after the last match.
</P>
<P>
The quarter-finals are scheduled on September 11, with the
finals being held on September 13.
</P>
<P>
Results of drawing for the preliminaries:
</P>
<P>
Group A: Poland, Germany, Kenya, Dominica (in Gdansk)
</P>
<P>
Group B: Cuba, Japan, Italy, Mauritius (in Gdansk)
</P>
<P>
Group C: Brazil, Russia, Argentina, Yugoslavia (in Cetniewo)
</P>
<P>
Group D: China, South Korea, Ukraine, Czech Republic (in
Cetniewo).
</P>
