<HEADLINE> Snowfall in Argentina Blocks Highway Leading to Chile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 25 (Xinhua) -- About 500 vehicles were
stuck today in different localities of the province of Mendoza
in western Argentina where heavy snowfalls blocked the main
route to Chile.
</P>
<P>
According to Emergency Operations Center authorities, the snow
which has fallen in the past 10 days has accumulated up to three
meters high close to the border town of Cuavas and the Cristo
Redentor international tunnel.
</P>
<P>
There has been no snow in the last 24 hours but more is
predicted soon and cold winds persist in the region, they added.
</P>
<P>
Residents have enough food to last them for a while, the
sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
