<HEADLINE> Countries Request Aid From Cuba in Sugar Cane Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Ecuador, El Salvador, Guatemala
and Mexico requested assistance from Cuba in the production of
sugar cane.
</P>
<P>
The request was based on the fact that Cuba is one of the
countries with the best technology in this field, said the Cuban
authorities today.
</P>
<P>
The request was made by delegates from those four countries
during the International Half Century Meeting of sugar cane
researchers held in Jovellanos, western province of Msatanzas.
</P>
<P>
According to spokespersons of the meeting, Ecuador, El
Salvador, Guatemala and Mexico asked Cuba for an exchange of
varieties and technology about genetic development to ward off
the pests and diseases that affect their plants.
</P>
<P>
Cuba is the leading country in sugar cane biotechnology
together with Australia, Brazil, the United States and South
Africa. Sugar is Cuba's main source of hard currency earner.
</P>
</TEXT>
