<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seles, Novotna Cruise into Wimbledon Second Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WIMBLEDON, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Second seed Monica Seles and
third seed Jana Novotna defeated their opponents here on Wednesday
with the other scheduled clashes simply being washed away by the
consistent rainfalls at the Wimbledon Championships.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav-born tough girl dominiated the whole match and
gave her nervous Australian opponent little hope of turning the
tide. Although the rain intervened at the crucial second set,
Seles ran away with a convincing straight sets victory 6-0, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
The world number four tennis player condeded that her serve
remains a shadow of its former self since she ended her two-year
absence from the tennis world.
</P>
<P>
"I'm not in the ideal physical shape I would like to be. I'm
trying to improve it," she told reporters after her easy victory.
</P>
<P>
Yet, Novotna met fierce resistance from German Wiltrud Probst,
dropped the second set before the Czech veteran displayed powerful
tennis at the decider to snatch the victory 6-4, 4-6, 6-0.
</P>
<P>
"She was playing really well and hit a lot of winners. The
second set was the best she has ever played against me," Novotna
said.
</P>
<P>
The other 77 scheduled matches would have to be carried over to
Thursday, but the wet forecast for the rest of the week is almost
bad omen to both players and thousands of tennis fans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
